data.description: Nestled in the highly coveted Historic Plaque neighborhood stands this stunning 1899 Victorian home, boasting timeless elegance and charming features. Set on a fenced corner lot with a blooming garden, this residence exudes curb appeal and tranquility. The neighborhood offers a serene atmosphere, with schools and parks just a leisurely stroll away. Meticulously cared for, the home showcases original hardwood floors, solid wood doors, and glass French doors, preserving its historic allure. The versatile den, complete with a half bath, can easily double as an extra bedroom or home office. The kitchen is a chef's delight, featuring stainless steel appliances, wrap-around maple cabinets, and a pantry for ample storage. With original leaded glass windows and marble flooring in the main bathroom, luxury and comfort abound. Take advantage of the many Elgin city grants available for the Historic Area and make this gracious Victorian retreat your own.
